(411, 63, 89, 'Adobe LiveCycle Designer (for creating Acrobat Forms) - Complete', 'Adobe LiveCycle Designer (for creating Acrobat Forms) – Complete\n\nCourse Description\nAdobe Designer is a client-based point-and-click graphical form design tool. This course focuses on using the software to create XML business forms for distribution as PDF or HTML.\n\nPrerequisites\n• There are no prerequisites for this course.\n\nCOURSE DETAILS\n\nDesigner Workspace\n• Layout Editor\n• Palettes\n• Customizing the Workspace\n\nUnderstanding Forms\n• Authoring a Form\n• Planning a Form\n• Form Components\n\nWorking with Form Designs\n• Using Template Manager\n• Setting Form Design Properties\n• Setting up Master and Body Pages\n• Setting Form Tab Order\n\nWorking with Objects\n• Object Types\n• Object Properties\n\nImporting Forms from Other Applications\n• PDF\n• Word\n• InfoPath\n\nCreating Interactive Forms\n• Adding Interactivity\n• Creating Dynamic Forms\n• Making Forms Secure\n• Testing Forms\n\nCreating Accessible Forms\n• Designing Accessible Forms\n\nWorking with Data Sources\n• Connecting to a Data Source\n• Binding Fields to a Data Source\n\nCreating Calculations and Scripts\n• Objects that Support Calculations and Scripts\n• Associating a Script with an Event\n• Using the Script Editor\n• Using JavaScript', '2.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/adobe-livecycle-designer-for-creating-acrobat-forms-complete/?loc=Vancouver', '', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(412, 63, 89, 'Adobe Photoshop - Level 1 / Intro', 'Adobe Photoshop – Level 1 / Intro\n\nCourse Description\nAdobe Photoshop has been a dominant program in the photographic community for years. Photoshop lets you create professional looking photographs, touch-ups and special effects and filters for both print and the Internet. This course is intended for students who want to learn the basics of photographic touch-ups, adjustments and enhancements, and become familiar with basic Photoshop tools\nNOTE: Items marked with an asterisk* are only taught for version CS5.\n\nPrerequisites\nThe prerequisites for this course are an introductory course to Windows or a solid working knowledge of Windows. A solid working knowledge of basic office software skills is required.\n\nCOURSE OUTLINE\n\nPHOTOSHOP BASICS\n• Explore Photoshop Interface and Workspace Elements\n• Arrange Toolbox and Panels\n• Understand File Types\n• Open, New and Save Options\n• Use the Help and Window Menus\n• Use the Info and Navigator Panels\n• Use the Hand, Zoom and View tools\n• Explore View Menu Options\n• Display One Image in Two Windows \n• Use the View Toolbar\n• Use Tabs and Tiling\n• Work with Rulers, Grids and Guides\n• Change the Screen Display Mode \n• Switch Workspaces\n• Create and Save Workspaces\n\nWORKING WITH IMAGE AREAS\n• Pixel and Resolutions Basics\n• Vector vs Raster Images\n• Place Images\n• Resample an Image\n• Use Auto Resolution\n• Recolor the Work Canvas \n• Change Dimensions and Resolution \n• Resize an Image \n• Change the Canvas \n• Flip and Rotate the Canvas\n• Crop, Flip, Rotate and Trim an Image\n• Rule of Thirds for Crop Tool*\n• Straighten Images with Ruler*\n \nMENU BASED IMAGE ADJUSTMENTS\n• Image Adjustment Basics\n• Change the Image Mode\n• Auto-Adjust an Image\n• Adjust Exposure, Brightness and Contrast\n• Use Variations\n\nCOLOUR BASICS\n• Colour management RGB vs CMYK\n• Use Image Modes and Channels\n• Use the Colour Panel\n• Use the Swatches Panel\n• Foreground and Background Colors \n• Use the Eyedropper and Colour Sampler Tools\n• Use Colour Ring for Colour Sampler*\n• Use the Colour Replacement Tool\n• Adjust an Image Using Replace Colors \n• Convert to Grayscale \n• Use the Channel Panel\n• Work with Spot Colour Channels\n• Create a Duotone picture\n\nMAKE, MANIPULATE AND EDIT SELECTIONS\n• Use the Select Menu\n• Working with the Marquee Tools \n• Working with the Lasso Tools \n• Using the Quick Selection Tool and the Refine Edge Tool \n• Using the Magic Wand \n• Using Color Range to make a Selection \n• Adding to or Subtracting from a Selection \n• Use Edge Detection to Refine Edges*\n• Smooth a Selection Edge \n• Invert, Skew, and Feather Selections\n• Use the Masks Panel to Refine Edges\n• Use Selection and Mask Refinement Tools*\n• Decontaminate Colour Selections*\n• Cut, Copy, Paste, Move, Deselect, Clear, Duplicate and Delete\n• Use Paste in Place*\n• Move, Rotate, Resize and Scale a Selection \n• Save a Selection\n\nWORK WITH LAYERS\n• Create, Delete, Move, Flip, Hide, Link and Lock Layers \n• Transform, Arrange and Group Layers\n• Apply Layer Transparency\n• Make Adjustments with Layers\n• Use the Eraser Tools\n• Use Content Aware Scaling\n• Use Content Aware Fill*\n• Apply Layer Styles and Effects\n• Merge Layers \n• Export Layers\n• Fill a Selection or a Layer \n• Apply a Stroke to a Selection or a Layer\n\nRETOUCH IMAGES\n• Use the Dodge, Sponge and Burn Tools\n• Use the Smudge, Blur and Sharpen Tools\n• Use the Clone, Stamp, and Healing tools\n• Reverse Direction of Clone Source*\n• Use the History Panel\n• Create and Use Snapshots\n• Use Patch and History Brush Tools\n• Use Automatic Lens Correction*\n• Remove Red Eye\n• Adjust Brightness and Contrast \n• Adjust Hue, Brightness and Saturation\n• Adjust Shadows and Highlights\n\nGETTING CREATIVE\n• Use the Paintbrush or Airbrush Tool \n• Use Brush Previews*\n• Use the Mixer Brush Tool*\n• Use Bristle Tips*\n• Use the Type tools\n• Use Character and Paragraph Panels\n• Warp Text\n\nWORK WITH FILTERS AND GRADIENTS\n• Use the Filter Gallery\n• Apply Different Filters\n• Modify Filters\n• Apply, Create and Edit a Gradient Preset \n• Save the Current Gradients to a File \n• Use Alternate Gradient Libraries \n• Restore the Default Gradients \n• Change the Opacity of Gradient Colors \n• Create a Multicolor Wash \n• Apply a Gradient Map to a Layer\n• Use Graduated Neutral Density Filters*\n\nOUTPUT\n• Proof Colours\n• Modify File Info\n• The Print Options Dialog Box \n• The Page Setup Dialog Box  \n• Save an Image as a Different File Type\n\nOPTIONS\n• Modify Menus\n• Modify Program Preferences\n\n* CS5 Only', '2.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/adobe-photoshop-level-1-intro/?loc=Vancouver', '', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(413, 63, 88, 'ASPMVC5: Microsoft ASP.NET MVC 5 Web Developer Training', 'ASPMVC5: Microsoft ASP.NET MVC 5 Web Developer Training\n\nCourse Description\nThis four-day, hands-on, workshop introduces you to everything you need to build web applications with the latest version of the Microsoft ASP.NET MVC framework. Taught by former Microsoft ASP.NET Senior Program Manager Stephen Walther, this workshop provides you with deep insights into all of the major features of ASP.NET MVC. Expect plenty of hands-on labs!\n \nAudience\nThis course is intended for any Developer interested in building web applications using ASP.NET MVC. This class also is appropriate for ASP.NET Web Forms developers who need to learn how to migrate to ASP.NET MVC.\n \nPrerequisites\nBefore attending this course, students should be familiar with:\n• The .NET Framework, the C# programming language and any knowledge of SQL Server is helpful but not required.\n \nWhat you will learn\nAfter completing this course, you will have an in-depth understanding of:\n• How to create models, views, controllers, and routes and how these elements of a MVC application fit together.\n• How to compose MVC views from layouts and partials, and how you can validate form data\n• Retrieving and storing information in a database.\n• Use LINQ and the Entity Framework to interact with a SQL Server database\n• Use patterns such as the Repository Pattern and Dependency Injection to write more maintainable and testable code.\n• How to build secure ASP.NET applications and how to create Single Page Applications (SPAs).\n• Use jQuery, KnockoutJS, and the ASP.NET Web API to build applications that execute in the browser.\n \n1. Model, View Controller Day\nThe goal of the first day is to understand how to create models, views, controllers, and routes and how these elements of a MVC application fit together.\n• Using the Visual Studio 2013 One ASP.NET Project Template\n• Creating a simple ASP.NET MVC application\n• Understanding Routing, Models, View, Controllers\n• Using the Razor View Engine\n• Creating Strongly-Typed Views\n \n2. View and Validation Day\nThe goal of this second day is to understand how you can compose MVC views from layouts and partials, and how you can validate form data.\n• Working with MVC Helpers\n• Validating form data\n• Using ASP.NET MVC Layouts\n• Using ASP.NET MVC Partials\n• Using ASP.NET MVC Templates\n• Using ASP.NET MVC Areas\n\n3. Database Day\nThe third day is focused on retrieving and storing information in a database. You learn how to use LINQ and the Entity Framework to interact with a SQL Server database.  You also learn how to take advantage of patterns such as the Repository Pattern and Dependency Injection to write more maintainable and testable code.\n• An introduction to LINQ\n• Building a database-driven application with the Microsoft Entity Framework\n• Using the Repository Pattern\n• Using Dependency Injection frameworks\n• Creating Unit Tests and using Mock Object frameworks\n\n4. Security and Single Page App Day  (SPA Day)\nOn this final day of the workshop, you learn how to build secure ASP.NET applications and how to create Single Page Applications (SPAs). You learn how to use jQuery, KnockoutJS, and the ASP.NET Web API to build applications that execute in the browser.\n\nSecurity\n• Common ASP.NET Security vulnerabilities and how to avoid them\n• Securing your web application with new ASP.NET Identity system\n\nSingle Page Apps\n• Performing Ajax requests with jQuery\n• Exposing data to the client with the ASP.NET Web API\n• Building client-side MVVM applications with KnockoutJS', '4.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/aspmvc4-microsoft-asp-net-mvc-4-web-developer-training/?loc=Vancouver', '', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(414, 63, 82, 'ATM002: Applied Time Management Using Outlook', 'ATM002: Applied Time Management Using Outlook\n\nCourse Description \nThis workshop is for people who want to improve their time management skills and practice using the fundamentals of Outlook to become more productive and better organized.\nParticipants will gain insights into time management by learning how to set SMART goals and priorities that stick. Make Outlook work your way while getting a handle on your workload and deal with emails more efficiently.\nPart of ctc TrainCanada’s applied learning approach is to include lots of practice time in this workshop, to make it easier to form new habits.  You will return to the office feeling confident that you are better organized and more effective.\n\nParticipants in this program will learn:\n• How to set SMART goals to effectively manage workloads and projects\n• Understand your organizational style -what works and what needs to be improved\n• How to apply the fundamentals of time management using Outlook to become more productive\n• How to use Outlook tools to become more proficient to save time\n\nWho will benefit from this course?\n• Individuals who recognize they need to become better organized and manage their workloads and time more effectively\n• Individuals who are familiar with Outlook but want to become  more effective using Outlook tools\n\nCOURSE OUTLINE\n\nIntroduction and Course Overview\n• Get to know other participants and discuss what will take place during the workshop.  Participants will also have an opportunity to identify their personal learning objectives.\n\nSetting Goals\n• Use Outlook tasks to set and manage goals\nPrioritize effectively \n• Use Outlook’s Priority setting tools\nForm Good Habits\n• Let Outlook help you control repetitive tasks\nIdentify time over which you have control\n• Track how much time you spend on specific activities\nIdentify and use your energy cycle\n• Use Outlook’s scheduling system to plan activities\nDealing with Procrastination\n• Learn to use reminders and flags effectively\nManage your workload\n• Customizing your Outlook views\nDivide large tasks\n• Manage tasks effectively\nDelegate effectively\n• Use Outlook to delegate and track tasks\nManage meetings\n• Master Outlook’s calendar and scheduling functions\nWorkshop Wrap-Up\n• At the end of the day, participants will have an opportunity to ask final questions and create an action plan. ', '2.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/atm002-applied-time-management-using-outlook/?loc=Vancouver', '', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(415, 63, 88, 'Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) - Level 1 / Intro', 'Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) – Level 1 / Intro\n\nCourse Description\nThis course uses CSS Level 1 to perform tasks which cannot be done using HTML alone including text formatting overlapping layers and creating browser specific content.\n \nPrerequisites\nThis course requires fundamental knowledge of HTML including document design text formatting images hyperlinks tables and frames. A previous introduction to DHTML would be extremely helpful.\n \nUNDERSTAND CSS\n• What is a StyleWhat are Cascading Style SheetsVersions of CSSTypes of CSS RulesThe Parts of a CSS RuleKinds of HTML Tags\n\nCSS BASICS\n• Add CSS to an HTML TagAdd CSS to a Web PageAdd CSS to a Web SiteDefine an HTML TagDefine ClassesDefine IdsCreate Inline HTML TagsCreate Block-Level HTML TagsDefine Tags with the Same RulesDefine Tags in ContextMake a Definition ImportantInherit Properties from ParentManage Existing or Inherited Property ValuesDetermine the Cascade OrderSet the CSS for PrintAdd Comments to CSSStyle-Sheet Strategies\n\nFONT CONTROLS\n• Understand Typography on the WebUse Type on the WebSet the FontDownload FontsUse Browser Safe FontsSet the Font SizeMake Text ItalicSet BoldBolderBoldestCreate MinicapsSet Multiple Font Values\n\nTEXT CONTROLS\n• Adjust KerningAdjust Word SpacingAdjust LeadingSet Text CaseAlign Text LeftRightand CenterAlign Text VerticallyIndent ParagraphsDecorate TextControl White SpaceSet Page Breaks for Print\n\nLIST AND MOUSE CONTROLS\n• Set up a ListSet the Bullet StyleCreate a Hanging IndentCreate your Own BulletsChange the Mouse Pointers Appearance\n\nCOLOUR AND BACKGROUND CONTROLS\n• Set the BackgroundSet Individual Background PropertiesSet a Foreground Colour\n\nBORDER AND MARGIN CONTROLS\n• Understand the Elements BoxSet the Width and Height of an ElementSet an Elements’s MarginsSet an Elements BorderDecorate an Elements BorderSet an Elements PaddingSet a Tables Borders and MarginsWrap Text Around an