(433, 63, 89, 'Microsoft Excel 2013 - Level 1 / Intro', 'Microsoft Excel 2013 – Level 1 / Intro\n\nCourse Description \nUsing Microsoft Excel, students will learn how create spreadsheets, navigate in a workbook and a worksheet, enter, edit data as well as learn how to set print options within Excel.\n \nPrerequisites\nThe prerequisites for this course are an introductory course to Windows or a solid working knowledge of Windows.\nCOURSE CONTENT\n\nWorking with Microsoft Excel and the Interface\n• Explore the user interface\n• Understand the Ribbon and Contextual Tabs\n• Data Entry to Create a New Workbook\n• Open an Existing Workbook\n• Using Excel Templates\n• Understanding how to Navigate in Excel\n• Using the Three Mouse Tools\n• Using the Three Modes of Excel\n• Review Excel Options\n• Using Help\n• Backstage View\n• Personalize Save and AutoRecover Locations\n• Customize the Quick Access Toolbar\n• Export Your Customization File\n• Enable Add-in’s\n• Review the Trust Center Settings\n• Understand the Difference between Save and SaveAs\n• Customizing the Status Bar\n \nUnderstanding and Working with Data\n• How to enter, edit, and delete data \n• What is a Label and a Value\n• How to Select Data\n• Using Autofill and Autocomplete\n• Cut, copy, paste and Paste Special\n• Undo, Redo, Repeat\n• Spell Check a Worksheet\n• Using Find, Replace and GoTo\n• Inserting/Deleting cells, worksheets, rows or columns\n\nUsing Basic Formulas and Functions\n• The difference between a formula and function\n• Order of Operations\n• How to create formulas\n• How to use simple functions\n• Using AutoSum\n• How to copy and paste or move formulas\n• Using the Fill Handle\n• Using Relative and Absolute Cell References\n \nFormatting Workbook Elements\n• Formatting Using the Home Tab\n• Formatting Using Dialog Boxes\n• Formatting Using the Mini-Toolbar\n• Using and Modifying Conditional Formatting\n• Using Borders & Shading\n• Using Number Formats\n• Cell Alignment\n• Using the Format Painter\n• Creating and Modifying Styles\n• Naming, Move or Copy, Colour Sheets \n• Changing Views and Setting Print Area\n \nDefine Print Area\n• Clearing Print Area\n• Working with Page Break Preview\n• Using Page Layout View\n• Setting Print Titles\n• Managing Multiple Windows\n• Arranging All\n• Splitting the Workbook Window\n• Freezing and UnFreezing Panes\n• Adding Headers and Footers\n• Using the View tab on the Ribbon\n \nCharting\n• Introduction to Simple Charts\n• Defining Axis\n• Saving a Chart as a Template\n• Customizing Chart Elements', '1.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/microsoft-excel-2013-level-1-intro/?loc=Vancouver', '', 2, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(434, 63, 89, 'Microsoft Excel 2013 - Level 2 / Med.', 'Microsoft Excel 2013 – Level 2 / Med.\n\nCourse Description\nUsing Microsoft Excel, students will learn to how to create advanced worksheets using Excel’s advanced features for filtering and sorting data.  Students will also learn the power of Pivot Tables and how to use Slicers to filter data with the click of a mouse button. Students will also use advanced formulas, tables, graphics and PivotCharts to enhance their workbooks.\n \nPrerequisites\n• Course prerequisites include taking Excel 2013 Level 1 or an equivalent in working knowledge of the software.\n\nCourse Details\n \nAdvanced Formulas for Data Analysis with Logical and Lookup Functions\n• Create Range Names Manually\n• Create Range Names by Selection\n• Manage Range Names\n• Specialized Functions PMT, DSUM and more\n• Logical and Lookup Functions, VLOOKUP, IF \n \nUsing Tables \n• Create Tables \n• Using the Table Tools Contextual tab\n• Using Table Options\n• Modify Tables and Convert to Range\n• Summarize a Table with a PivotTable\n• Using PivotTable Summary Functions\n• Sorting and Filtering Data in Tables\n\nExcel Charts\n• Create & Format Charts\n• Modify Chart Layouts and Structures\n• Change Chart Types, Options, Location\n• Change Source Data\n• Save a Chart as a Template\n• Advanced Charts\n• Adding Trendlines\n \nExcel Reports with PivotTables, PivotCharts and Slicers\n• Creating a PivotTable from a Data Range\n• Using the PivotTable Contextual Tabs\n• Refreshing Data from a Range vs Table\n• Using Slicers\n• Using the Slicer Contextual Tab\n• Creating a Switchboard Using Slicers\n• Using PivotCharts\n• Filtering Data using PivotCharts\n• Using the PivotCharts Contextual Tabs\n \nAnnotating Using Graphical Element\n• Using Textboxes\n• Modifying Textboxes using the Drawing Contextual Tab\n• Inserting ClipArt Modifying ClipArt \n• Adding Shapes and Laying Shapes\n• Using SmartArt \n• Modifying SmartArt using the Contextual Tabs\n\nPersonalizing your Workbooks \n• Using Excel Options to Customize Workbooks\n• Using, Creating and Managing Excel Themes\n• Creating and Using Personal Template\n• Protecting Your Workbook formulas\n• Encrypting Your Excel Files', '1.0', '0.00', 'http://www.traincanada.com/course/microsoft-excel-2013-level-2-med/?loc=Vancouver', '', 2, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(435, 63, 89, 'Microsoft Excel 2013 - Level 3 / Advanced', 'Microsoft Excel 2013 – Level 3 / Advanced\n\nCourse Description\nStudents will learn to more of the advanced features of Excel: Using Macros to automate repetitive tasks, auditing worksheets, sharing data, analyzing data, importing and exporting data.\n\nPrerequisites\nCourse prerequisites include taking Excel 2013 Level 2 or an equivalent in working knowledge of the software.\n\nCourse Details\n• Refresh Using the Interface (For Upgrade Students)\n \nBackstage View\n• Ribbon Navigation\n• Mini-Toolbar\n• Status Bar\n• Shortcut Key Tips\n• Contextual Tabs\n\nAutomating Excel’s Advanced Functionality\n• View and Update Workbook Properties\n• Create a Macro\n• Create a Relative Reference Macro\n• Use Cell Styles\n• Add and Modify Conditional Formatting\n• Validate Data\n• Add Input Messages for Users\n• Add Error Messages to Advise of Invalid Data\n\nFormula and Worksheet Auditing \n• Display Formulas\n• Audit Cell Formulas\n• Tracing Formula Precedence\n• Tracing Dependants\n• Understanding Error Messages\n• Using the Watch Window\n• Using Grouping and Outlining\n• Using SubTotals\n\nAnalyzing and Presenting Data \n• Creating Sparklines\n• Working with Scenarios\n• Working with What-If-Analysis\n• Using the Analysis Toolpack\n• Use PowerPivot\n• Use Goal Seek\n• Using One and Two Input Data Tables\n \nWorking with Multiple Workbooks \n• Consolidate Date Using Formulas\n• Consolidate Function\n• Linking workbooks\n• Merging Workbooks\n• Using the Slicer Contextual Tab\n• Importing and Exporting Data\n\nAnnotating Using Graphical Element\n• Using Textboxes\n• Modifying Textboxes using the Drawing Contextual Tab\n• Inserting ClipArt Modifying ClipArt \n• Adding Shapes and Laying Shapes\n• Using SmartArt \n• Modifying SmartArt using the Contextual Tabs\n\nPersonalizing your Workbooks\n• Using Excel Options to Customize Workbooks\n• Using, Creating and Managing Excel Themes\n• Creating and Using Personal Template